          <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US">Effective date: 1.7.2015</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">PIXEL FEDERATION, s.r.o., a Slovak republic limited liability company, with its registered office at Einsteinova 19, 851 01 Bratislava, Slovakia, Identification No. (ICO) 36 816&nbsp;388, registered in the Commercial Register maintained by District Court Bratislava I., Section Sro, Entry No. 47333/B and its affiliates (&ldquo;PIXEL&rdquo;) has accepted this PIXEL FEDERATION, s.r.o.&rsquo;s PRIVACY POLICY (&ldquo;Privacy Policy&rdquo;) to explain how and for which purpose PIXEL processes, i.e.: acquires, collects, uses, treats, stores/holds discloses etc., the information acquired/collected in connection with PIXEL&rsquo;s products, services and websites including but not limited to PIXEL&acute;s online games - TrainStation, Diggy&acute;s Adventure, Emporea 2: Realms of War &amp; Magic, BIG Shopkeeper and in connection with other PIXEL Services (PIXEL Services as specified below). This Privacy Policy governs your use of PIXEL Services (as specified below). Use of the PIXEL Services (as specified below) is also governed by PIXEL&rsquo;s EULA, which is incorporated herein by reference - posted on the PIXEL portal site <a href="http://portal.pixelfederation.com/">http://portal.pixelfederation.com</a>.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">For purposes of this Privacy Policy "Software" means all software programs distributed, published or otherwise made available by PIXEL including but not limited to games accessed by means of a browser or other online communication method and downloadable/installable games for personal computer, mobile and other devices, especially including but not limited to the PIXEL&acute;s online games - TrainStation, Diggy&acute;s Adventure, Emporea 2: Realms of War &amp; Magic, BIG Shopkeeper (each of them individually "GAME&rdquo; or &ldquo;App&rdquo; or together &ldquo;GAMES" or &ldquo;Apps&rdquo;) offered for example on the PIXEL portal site <a href="http://portal.pixelfederation.com/">http://portal.pixelfederation.com</a> ("PORTAL"). Software also includes updates and upgrades as well as accompanying manual(s), packaging and other written, files, electronic or on-line materials or documentation, and any and all copies of such software and its materials. &ldquo;Services&rdquo; means all services made available by PIXEL, including but not limited to PIXEL branded websites, services accessed through mobile games, services accessed by means of a browser or by other online communication method. Software and Services are collectively referred to as &ldquo;PIXEL Service&rdquo; or &ldquo;PIXEL Services&rdquo;. PIXEL Services means the hardware or software tool by which the Personal Data/Usage Data (as specified below) of the End-User are processed.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">PIXEL&acute;s Services acquires/collect some Personal Data (as specified below) from its Users (&bdquo;End-Users&ldquo;). This Privacy Policy describes the ways PIXEL processes, i.e.: acquires, collects, treats, uses, hold/stores, disclose, manages etc., the data including Personal data (as specified below) that you as an End-User provide or PIXEL acquires/collects in connection with PIXEL Services. Please note that the scope of this Privacy Policy is limited to Data (as specified below) acquired/collected or received by PIXEL through your use of the PIXEL Services. PIXEL is not responsible for the actions of third party people or companies, the content of their sites, the use of Data (as specified below) you provide to them or any products or services they may offer. Any link to those sites does not constitute PIXEL&acute;s sponsorship of or affiliation with those people or companies. Before accessing or using the PIXEL Service, including browsing any PIXEL website or accessing a GAME, you must agree to this Privacy Policy and the PIXEL&rsquo;s EULA. You may also be required to register an account on the PIXEL Service (&ldquo;Account&rdquo;). By registering for an Account or otherwise using the PIXEL Service, you confirm and represent that you are age 18 or older and that you are acquainted with this Privacy Policy and that you understand and agree to this Privacy Policy. If you are age under 18, you confirm and represent that your legal guardian is acquainted with and understands this Privacy Policy and has agreed to this Privacy Policy. If you access the PIXEL Service from a Social Networking Site (&ldquo;SNS&rdquo;) - such as Facebook or Google+, or from a application platforms (&ldquo;Application Platform&rdquo;) - such as Apple&rsquo;s Appstore, Google Play (Android) and Windows Phonestore, you shall comply with its privacy policy (including its terms of service/use) as well as this Privacy Policy [for purposes of this Privacy Policy Social Networking Site/SNS or Application Platform means the specific SNS or Application Platform and/or the operator of the specific SNS or Application Platform also]. By accepting this Privacy Policy, registering to, installing, using or otherwise accessing the PIXEL Services or any materials included in or with the PIXEL services, you hereby represent and confirm that you accept/agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy without reservation, i.e. you are expressing your voluntarious agreement to this Privacy Policy and to the processing of your data including your Personal Data (End-User&acute;s Personal Data) provided by you to PIXEL or acquired/collected by PIXEL from you in relation to providing PIXEL Services for the purposes and in the manner provided in this Privacy Policy, mainly for the purpose of exploitation of the PIXEL Services, which means that you give an explicit and informed voluntarious consent to PIXEL (you authorizes PIXEL) to the processing (to process), i.e. specially: to the acquisition (to acquire), collecting (to collect), use (to use), treatment (treat), hold of data/storage (to hold/to retain/to store), of data about you including your Personal Data (End-User&acute;s Personal Data) and Usage Data, and diclosure (to disclose) of your Personal Data (End-User&acute;s Personal Data) and Usage Data in accordance with this Privacy Policy to the third person, or you agree that PIXEL is entitled to delegate performance of mentioned activities to the third person (Data Processor as specified below) whereby above mentioned consent of you as an End-User is given to PIXEL indefinitely,and this above mentioned consent of you as an End-User is given to PIXEL even if the place of Data processing is situated in a country which under the relevant legislation of the European Union does not ensure an adequate level of protection (e.g. USA), and therefore you agree to the transfer of your Personal Data and Usage Data to a country which under the relevant legislation of the European Union does not ensure an adequate level of protection. In case you revoke above mentioned consent PIXEL shall thenceforth be entitled to process and treat your Personal Data for the statistics purposes while the Personal Data will be in anonymous form. By accepting this Privacy Policy, registering to, installing, using or otherwise accessing the PIXEL Services or any materials included in or with the PIXEL services, you hereby represent and confirm that you have been instructed about the voluntariness of provision of your Personal Data (disclosure of your Personal Data), about your right to revoke the given consent to process your Personal Data at any time and also about your other rights in relation to the processing of your Personal Data according to paragraphs 28 to 30 of the Act No. 136/2014 Coll. on Protection of Personal Data as amended or according to other relevant generally binding regulation. If you do not agree with the processing of your data including your Personal Data (End-User&acute;s Personal Data) in the manner provided in this Privacy Policy, i.e. if you do not agreewith this Privacy Policy (if you do not accept the terms of this Privacy Policy), please do not accept, register to, install, use or otherwise access the PIXEL Services, as the use of the PIXEL Services is not possible unless the End-User accepts this Privacy Policy without reservation. Use of the PIXEL Services is void where prohibited. The meaning of the terms Personal Data, Usage Data, Data and End-User is specified below.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">PIXEL reserves the right, in regard of the change of relevant legal regulations, the change of market situation, the change of its business policy or at its discretion, unilaterally to change, modify, cancel, add or remove portions of this Privacy Policy or the Privacy Policy of any GAME (hereinafter just &bdquo;Change of the Privacy Policy&ldquo;) at any time without prior notice by posting the updated/amended Privacy Policy including the day of its effectiveness (Effective date) on or within the PIXEL Services (including but not limited on PORTAL or in any of the GAMES), such a Change of the Privacy Policy will be valid and effective as of the &nbsp;day stated in the updated/amended Privacy Policy as its Effective date. It is strongly recommended to check the actual/current Privacy Policy, especially through <a href="http://portal.pixelfederation.com/"><span lang="en-US">http://portal.pixelfederation.com</span></a>, whereby the date of the last modification (Effective date) is stated at the beginning of Privacy Policy. You (as an End-User) are responsible to be acquainted with the latest version of Privacy Policy. You will be deemed to have accepted such Change of the Privacy Policyby continuing to use the PIXEL Services, because you confirm that you are acquainted with the Change of the Privacy Policy and that you agree with the Change of the Privacy Policy without reservation by continuing to use the PIXEL Services. If at any point you do not agree to any portion of the then-current version of our (this) Privacy Policy or any other PIXEL policy, rules or codes of conduct relating to your use of the PIXEL Service, your license to use the PIXEL Service shall immediately terminate, and you must immediately stop using the PIXEL Service, i.e. if the End-User objects to the Change of the Privacy Policy, the End-User must cease using the PIXEL Services and can request that PIXEL erase the Personal Data. Unless stated otherwise, the then-current Privacy Policy applies to all Personal Data PIXEL has about End-Users.</p>
