<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Definitions:</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Personal Data</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Different kind of information can be considered as the Personal Data. PIXEL defines Personal Data as information regarding a natural person, a legal person, an institution or an association, which is, or can be, identified, even indirectly, by reference to any other information, including a personal identification number; Personal Data means any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person/individual, while such person/individual is one who can be identified directly or indirectly in particular by reference to a identifier of general application or by reference to one or more factors specific to his physical, physiological, psychic, mental, economic, cultural or social identity (within the text of this Privacy Policy just &bdquo;Personal Data&ldquo;).</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Usage Data</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">In addition to Personal Data, PIXEL processes, i.e.: acquires, collects, treats, uses, retains/stores or discloses etc., in accordance with this Privacy Policy a variety of information/data that could not be used to identify or contact the End-User, which can be/are used to enhance the quality of the GAMES and other PIXEL Services. Usage Data are informations acquired/collected automatically from the PIXEL Services (or third party services employed in the PIXEL Services), which can depending on specific PIXEL Service include: the IP (Internet Protocol) addresses or domain names of the computers/devices utilized by the End-Users who use the PIXEL Services, the URI addresses (Uniform Resource Identifier), the time of the request, the method utilized to submit the request to the server, the size of the file received in response, the numerical code indicating the status of the server's answer (successful outcome, error, etc.), the country of origin, the features of the browser and the operating system utilized by the End-User, other general information about the End-User&acute;s interaction with PIXEL Services (e.g., the End-User&acute;s browser type, referring and exit URLs, click amounts, websites viewed, the amount of time spent viewing a particular website, the lenght of time of such activities, etc.), the various time details per visit/accessing the PIXEL Service (e.g., the time spent on each page within the PIXEL Services), information relating to the End-User&acute;s interaction with the GAMES/other PIXEL Services (e.g., the length of time the the End-User plays a GAME, the number and type of activities the End-User participates in during a particular session in the GAME, the End-User&acute;s scores) and the details about the path followed within the PIXEL Services with special reference to the sequence of pages visited, and other parameters about the device operating system and/or the End-User's IT environment (within the text of this Privacy Policy just &bdquo;Usage Data&ldquo;).</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Personal Data and Usage Data are collectively referred to as &ldquo;Data&rdquo;.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">End-User</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The individual using the PIXEL Services, which must coincide with or be authorized by the Data Subject, to whom the Personal Data refer (&bdquo;End-User&ldquo;).</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Data Subject</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The legal or natural person to whom the Personal Data refers to (&bdquo;Data Subject&ldquo;).</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Data Processor (or Data Supervisor)</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The natural person, legal person, public administration or any other body, association or organization authorized by the Data Controller to process the Personal Data in compliance with this Privacy Policy (&bdquo;Data Processor&ldquo; or &bdquo;Data Supervisor&ldquo;).</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Data Controller (or Owner)</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The natural person, legal person, public administration or any other body, association or organization with the right, also jointly with another Data Controller, to make decisions regarding the purposes, and the methods of processing of Personal Data and the means used, including the security measures concerning the operation and use of the PIXEL Services. The Data Controller, unless otherwise specified, is the Owner of the PIXEL Services (&bdquo;Data Controller&ldquo; or &bdquo;Owner&ldquo;).</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Cookie</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Small piece of data (small file) stored in the End-User's device that contains non-personal information/Usage Data (&bdquo;Cookie&ldquo;).</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Types of Personal Data/Usage Data acquired/collected:</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Among the types of Data that the Data Controller/PIXEL Services acquires/collects, by itself or through third parties, there are: Email, First Name, Surname, Country, City, Date of Birth, Gender, Cookie, Usage Data, Facebook friends and Password of the End-User. Other particular Personal Data acquired/collected may be described in other sections of this Privacy Policy or by dedicated explanation text contextually with the Data collection.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The Personal Data may be/are freely/voluntariously provided by the End-User, or acquired or collected automatically when using the PIXEL Services.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Any use of Cookies - or of other tracking tools - by the PIXEL Services or by the owners of third party services used by the PIXEL Services, unless stated otherwise, serves to identify End-Users and remember their preferences, for the sole purpose of providing the service required by the End-User.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Failure to provide certain Personal Data may make it impossible for the Apps/GAMES to provide its services.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The End-User assumes responsibility for the Personal Data of third parties published or shared through the PIXEL Services and declares to have the right to communicate or broadcast them, thus relieving the Data Controller of all responsibility.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Content generated by the End-User (&bdquo;User Content&ldquo;):</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">End-User may choose to share additional information/data about himself through the End-User&acute;s generated content. The content generated by the End-User may be defined as various kinds of content publicly available, that are produced/generated by the End-User (e.g., wall posts, messages, and actions with other End-Users) and it is possible that the generated content the End-User choose to provide may contain Personal Data/information. The End-User is aware that PIXEL cannot guarantee protection for information/data the End-User makes available publicly by means of comments, wall posts, etc. Additionally, it is likely that the content generated by the End-User will be disseminated broadly through third parties such as Facebook, other SNS or by other possible means. Further, the End-User should be aware that such public information/data may be taken away/withdrawed by third parties with access to it (such as other End-Users) and PIXEL cannot control those third parties' use of such information/data.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Mode and place of processing the Data:</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Methods of processing</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The Data Controller processes/uses/treats the Personal Data and Usage Data of End-Users in a proper manner and shall take appropriate security measures to prevent unauthorized access, disclosure, modification, or unauthorized destruction, providing, disclosure, damage and loss of the Personal Data and Usage Data of End-Users.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The Personal Data and Usage Data of End-Users processing is carried out using computers (devices) and/or IT enabled tools, following organizational procedures and modes strictly related to the purposes indicated. In addition to the Data Controller, in some cases, the Personal Data and Usage Data of End-Users may be accessible to certain types of persons in charge, involved with the operation of the site (administration, sales, marketing, legal service providers, system administration) or other external parties (such as third party technical service providers, mail carriers, hosting providers, IT companies, communications agencies, accountant/tax service providers) or other types of persons in charge providing services to the Data Controller (suppliers), appointed if necessary as Data Processors by the Owner. The list of these parties as Data Processors changes from time to time/updates, the updated list of these parties may be requested from the Data Controller at any time.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Place</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The Personal Data/Usage Data is processed/used/treated at the Data Controller's operating offices and in any other places where the parties involved with the processing are located. For further information, please contact the Data Controller.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Retention time</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The Personal Data/Usage Data are kept for an indefinite period of time, i.e. for the time necessary to provide the service requested by the End-User or stated by the purposes outlined in this document, and the End-User can always request that the Data Controller suspend or remove the Data.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The processing of the acquired/collected Data:</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The Personal Data/Usage Data concerning the End-User is acquired/collected to allow the PIXEL Services to provide its services, as well as for the following purposes: Access to third party services' accounts, Contacting the End-User, Infrastructure monitoring, Managing email addresses and sending messages, Registration and authentication, Analytics, Advertising, Remarketing and Behavioral Targeting, Heat mapping, Interaction with external social networks and platforms and Handling payments.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">There are specified purposes and manners for which/how PIXEL processes the Personal Data/Usage Data acquired/collected by PIXEL thereinafter in this Privacy Policy. In case of other manners or purposes of processing of the acquired/collected Data occur, this (the relevant) section of this Privacy Policy will be amended.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The Data used for each purpose is outlined in the specific sections of this document.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Facebook permissions asked by the PIXEL Services:</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The PIXEL Services may ask some Facebook permissions allowing it to perform actions with the End-User's Facebook account and to retrieve information, including Personal Data, from it.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">For more information about the following permissions, refer to the <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/docs/authentication/permissions/" target="_blank">Facebook permissions documentation</a> and to the <a href="https://www.facebook.com/about/privacy/" target="_blank">Facebook privacy policy</a>.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The permissions asked are the following:</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Basic information</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">By default, this includes certain End-User&rsquo;s Data such as id, name, picture, gender, and their locale. Certain connections of the End-User, such as the Friends, are also available. If the users (End-Users) have made more of their data public, more information will be available.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">About Me</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Provides access to the 'About Me' section of the profile.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Email</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Provides access to the End-User's primary email address.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">List of Friends</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Publish App Activity</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Allows the App/PIXEL Services to publish to the Open Graph using&nbsp;Built-in Actions, Achievements,&nbsp;Scores, or&nbsp;Custom Actions. The App/PIXEL Services can also publish other activity which is detailed in the Facebook's Publishing Permissions document.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Detailed information on the processing of Data:</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Data is collected for the following purposes and using the following services:</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Access to third party services' accounts</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">These services allow the PIXEL Services to access Data from your account on a third party service and perform actions with it. These services are not activated automatically, but require explicit authorization by the End-User.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Access to the Facebook account</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">This service allows the App/PIXEL Services to connect with the End-User's account on the Facebook social network, provided by Facebook Inc.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Permissions asked: About Me, Email, List of Friends and Publish App Activity.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Place of processing: USA &ndash; <a href="https://www.facebook.com/policy.php" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a></p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Advertising</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">These services allow Personal Data/Usage Data of the End-User to be utilized for advertising communication purposes displayed in the form of banners and other advertisements on the/within the PIXEL Services, possibly based on End-User interests. This does not mean that all Personal Data are used for this purpose. Information and conditions of use are shown below.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">By accepting the terms of this Privacy Policy the End-User grants permission to PIXEL to contact the End-User and send to or to provide the End-User with the advertisement or marketing announcements. To realize this contact the End-User agrees PIXEL to use Personal Data the End-User provides PIXEL with according to the terms of this Privacy Policy. By accepting the terms of this Privacy Policy the End-User grants permission to PIXEL to provide third person/party (PIXEL&rsquo;s advertising partners and contractors in relation to Advertising) with Personal Data of End-User according to the purpose of this Privacy Policy.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Some of the services listed below may use Cookies to identify End-Users or they may use the behavioral retargeting technique, i.e. displaying ads tailored to the End-User&rsquo;s interests and behavior, including those detected outside the App/GAME. For more information, please check the privacy policies of the relevant services.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
