<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Further information about Data:</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Push notifications</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The PIXEL Services may send push notifications to the End-User. Push notification, also called server push notification, is the delivery of information from a software application to a computing device without a specific request from an user, i.e. a push notification is a message or alert delivered by a centralized server to an endpoint device (within the text of this Privacy Policy just &bdquo;Push notifications&ldquo;).</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Selling goods and services online</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The Personal Data acquired/collected are used to provide the End-User with services or to sell goods, including payment and possible delivery.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The Personal Data acquired/collected to complete the payment may concern the credit card, the bank account used for the transfer, or any other means of payment envisaged. The kind of Data collected by the PIXEL Services depends on the payment system used.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Unique device identification</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The PIXEL Services may track End-Users by storing a unique identifier of their device, for analytics purposes or for storing End-Users' preferences.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Improvement of PIXEL Services</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The Data acquired/collected are used to improve the quality of the PIXEL Services, to improve the playability of the GAMES as well as to offer new features for the End-User within the PIXEL Services. PIXEL may for this purpose track End-Users&acute;s interaction with the PIXELServices and track the zones/areas in the content of which the End-Users are the most interested. The Data acquired/collected may be used also to optimalize/improve the content of the PIXEL Services by locating bugs/defects in the PIXEL Services. PIXEL may disclose general statistics collected directly by PIXEL/PIXEL Service (which will not include any information/data capable of identifying or contacting any particular End-User) to enhance customer service/PIXEL Services, to adjust the PIXEL Services according to the End-Users&acute; interests or to optimalize the PIXEL Services.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">What PIXEL does not do with Personal Data</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">PIXEL does not sell, rent or otherwise transfer the End-User&acute;s Personal Data to any third parties except as provided in this Privacy Policy. PIXEL does not disclose individual IP (Internet Protocol) addresses to any third parties except as provided in this Privacy Policy.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Information about Cookies:</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Cookies help to give the End-User faster access to websites the End-User has visited already before. Cookies also allow the End-User to accommodate/adjust his/her websites and optimalize his/her experiences in the PIXEL Services. PIXEL also uses Cookies to figure out the number of users visiting PORTAL and their interaction with the PIXEL Services. The End-User may delimit Cookies on his/her device by adjusting the preferences or options in his browser. The End-User is aware of the fact that limiting of Cookies may prevent the End-User from proper functioning/use of the PIXEL Services.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
