<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Additional information about Data processing, i.e. especially about Data acquisition, collection, use, treatment, hold/storage and disclosure:</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Legal purposes</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The End-User's Personal Data may be used for legal purposes by the Data Controller, in court or in the stages leading to possible legal action or in other legal procedures in/in front of other public authorities according to the applicable law, arising from improper use of the PIXEL Services or the related services.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The End-User is aware of the fact that the Data Controller may be required to reveal/disclose (PIXEL may reveal/disclose) Personal Data to the third subjects upon request of public authorities (including courts, state authorities or other public authorities in respect to applicable law), in other situations when it is required by the applicable law or in the situations when Data Controller is required to prevent any illegal activity or damage according to the applicable law.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Security</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">PIXEL performs its best efforts to protect/secure Data processed, i.e.: acquired, collected etc., by PIXEL and/or other information/data that the End-User shares with PIXEL/Pixel Services freely/voluntariously by using the encryption and authentication tools to protect its security on a server secured by a&nbsp;firewall without direct online connection. The End-User is aware of the fact that no online information/data transmission cannot be secured of any unauthorized access (attacking/hacking) and thatswhy PIXEL does not guarantee the security of any Data which are freely/voluntariously provided by the End-User, or acquired or collected automatically when using the PIXEL Services. The End-User is aware of the fact that PIXEL is not liable for any theft, loss or any other unauthorized access or damage to any Data processed by PIXEL and/or other information/data that the End-User shares with PIXEL/Pixel Services freely/voluntariously.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Additional information about End-User's Personal Data</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">In addition to the information contained in this Privacy Policy, the PIXEL Services may provide the End-User with additional and contextual information concerning particular services or the processing, i.e.: acquisition, collection, use, treatment, hold/storage and disclosure etc., of Personal Data upon request.</p>
