<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The rights of End-Users</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">End-Users have the right, at any time, to know whether their Personal Data has been stored and can consult the Data Controller to learn about their contents and origin, to verify their accuracy or to ask for them to be supplemented, cancelled, updated or corrected, or for their transformation into anonymous format or to block any Data held in violation of the law, as well as to oppose their treatment for any and all legitimate reasons. Request should be sent to the Data Controller at the contact information set out above or at the bottom of this document.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Legal information:</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Slovak law applies to this Privacy Policy, i.e. this Privacy Policy shall be governed by Slovak law, especially by the Act No. 136/2014 Coll. on Protection of Personal Data, by the EC Directive n. 95/46/EC and by the Directive 2002/58/EC as revised by Directive 2009/136/EC on the subject of Cookies.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Unless dictated otherwise by mandatory law, all disputes arising out of or in connection with this Privacy Policy between PIXEL and the End-User (including any disputes as to the validity and existence hereof and/or this clause, and the scope hereof) shall be finally settled by the relevant Slovak court having jurisdiction.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Jurisdiction is determined by the general territorial jurisdiction over the legislation in force in the Slovak Republic. PIXEL and End-User/s, in accordance with Art. 23 Council Regulation No 44/2001 on jurisdiction and the recognition and enforcement of judgments in civil and commercial matters, agree that the courts of the Slovak Republic are competent for the settlement of all disputes arising from and in any connection with this Privacy Policy between PIXEL and you as the End-User or any other third party, whereby the competent court for the proceedings in the first instance is The District Court Bratislava I. PIXEL shall not be prevented from taking proceedings relating to any dispute referred to in previous sentence in any other court of competent jurisdiction.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Miscellaneous terms:</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">The PIXEL Services are not dedicated to natural persons/individuals under the age of 18 years. By using the PIXEL Service, you confirm and represent that you are age 18 or older and that you are acquainted with this Privacy Policy and that you understand and agree to this Privacy Policy. If you are age under 18, you confirm and represent that your legal guardian is acquainted with and understands this Privacy Policy and has agreed to this Privacy Policy. If PIXEL becomes aware that the End-User is under the age of 18 and uses the PIXEL Services without prior consent of his/her legal guardian, PIXEL will remove the Personal Data of such an End-User's.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">A finding that any particular provision of this Privacy Policy is legally void shall not affect the validity of the entire Privacy Policy. In such a case such provision shall be replaced by provision that is legally valid and approximates the intent of the offending provision as much as possible. If any provisions of this Privacy Policy is held to be unenforceable for any reason, such provision shall be reformed only to the extent necessary to make it enforceable (corresponding as closely as possible to the parties&rsquo; (its) intention and the originally desired economic effect of the ineffective or unenforceable provision) and the remaining provisions of this Privacy Policy shall not be affected, i.e. if any provision of this Privacy Policy is or becomes ineffective or unenforceable, the remaining provisions of this Privacy Policy shall remain in full force and effect.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Rights and obligations under this Privacy Policy including acquired/collected Data itself are transferred to any legal succesors of the PIXEL and on each further legal successors.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">PIXEL may also transfer/assign its rights and obligations under this Privacy Policy, especially PIXEL&acute;s rights and obligations to the Data acquired/collected (including transfer/assignment of these acquired/collected Data itself), to a third party/entity that acquires the relevant business related to PIXEL Services or the copyrights to PIXEL Services from PIXEL, or to a third party/entity which acquires fifty per cent (50%) or more of the PIXEL&rsquo;s participation interest, or to a third party/entity a fifty per cent (50%) or more of participation interest of which is owned by PIXEL, or to a third party/entity in which PIXEL possesses the power and authority to exercise through its ownership interests a controlling influence over the management or the business of this third party/entity, without any impact on the End-User&acute;s ability to use the PIXEL Services continuously (i.e. that the Apps/GAMES provide its services continuously).</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">Third Party Beneficiary: PIXEL and you as an End-User acknowledge and agree that Application Platform and/or SNS and their/its subsidiaries, are third party beneficiaries of this Privacy Policy, and that upon the End-User&rsquo;s acceptance of the terms and conditions of this Privacy Policy Application Platform and/or SNS and their/its subsidiaries has/have the right (and deem/s to have accepted the right) to enforce the Privacy Policy against you as an End-User as a third party beneficiary thereof.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">This Privacy Policy relates solely to the PIXEL Services, i.e. to Personal Data/Usage Data processed, i.e.: acquired, collected, used, treated, held/stored, disclosed etc., by PIXEL. PIXEL Services may contain links to other websites. PIXEL is not responsible for the privacy practices of other websites. PIXEL encourages the End-Users to be aware when accessing other websites out of PIXEL Services to read the privacy statements of each and every website that collects personal information/data. This Privacy Policy applies solely to information collected by PIXEL.</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
<p lang="en-US" align="justify">If you have any questions or concerns about PIXEL&acute;s Privacy Policy, please contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@pixelfederation.com">privacy@pixelfederation.com</a> or at <a href="mailto:support@pixelfederation.com">support@pixelfederation.com</a>.</p>
